# EE4108 Machine Learning Project: CIFAR-10 Classification with Modified AlexNet

![CIFAR-10 Samples](https://www.cs.toronto.edu/~kriz/cifar-10-sample/bird6.png)  
*Final project for **EE4108 Machine Learning** at Aston University (2021), implementing and optimizing a CNN based on AlexNet architecture for CIFAR-10 image classification.*

---

## ðŸ“Œ Project Overview
**Goal:**  
Implement and optimize a convolutional neural network (CNN) inspired by **AlexNet** to classify images from the **CIFAR-10 dataset** (60,000 32x32 RGB images across 10 classes).

**Key Tasks:**  
1. **Base CNN Implementation** (Task-1)  
2. **Overfitting Reduction** via Dropout (Task-2)  
3. **Performance Boost** with BatchNorm (Task-3)  
4. **Architecture Modification**: All-Convolutional Network (Task-4)  
5. **Generalization Improvement** via Image Augmentation (Task-5) 
